In 1996 S&W brought out their J-Magnum frame capable of firing .357 magnum loads as well as .38+ loads of course . In 2001 the internal lock was added to all external hammer revolvers . For some reason S&W also put adjustable sights on a few of the models between 1996-2001 . 
I have carried this gun and at around 23 ounces it's easy to carry . I have shot about 100 rounds of 38 standard loads and exactly 10 rounds of .357 semi wad-cutters .

The gun is in good condition and locks up tight .

title: For Sale:  UHF Long Range / Long  Battery Life Transmitter Secret Spy Listening Bug & FREE Receiver
postcontent:
UHF Long Range / Long Battery Life Transmitter Spy Listening Bug & INCLUDED Receiver (100% Guaranteed!)
You will be amazed at the strange sounds you here at night when using this UHF Spy Bug in the forest when camping or hunting. This UHF Bug can also be attached to a digital recorder for saving all the recorded sounds for future playback. 

 This transmitter operates on Ultra High Frequency, (UHF) 434.120Mhz. This type of UHF transmitter is used by professionals worldwide because of its penetrating power and very clear reception. *Includes high quality transceiver with earphone option for private listening. 

This transmitter is PLL (Phase-Locked Loop) controlled and the frequency is very stable. 
Over 4000 feet!! transmission range in the open!

Long range and long life transmitter.
Works for 7 days when using 2 AA Duracell alkaline batteries.

Why is a UHF transmitter better than a VHF transmitter?                                              Traditionally most Spy Bugs are VHF (88Mhz-108Mhz) FM. 
They work well but there transmissions are not secure because you can use any FM radio to listen to the transmission ,this transmitter is on UHF and the transmission is very much more secure because you need a transceiver / scanner or a UHF receiver to listen to the transmission. 

This UHF Transmitter is PLL (Phase-Locked Loop) controlled.
What is PLL (Phase-Locked Loop)???
Phase-locked loops are widely used in radio, telecommunications, computers and other electronic applications. They generate very stable frequencies in addition to stabilizing a particular communications channel (keeping it set to a particular frequency) So making this Spy transmitters frequency very stable ,you can hold this transmitter and the frequency will not move.

Package contains:
1) UHF transmitter
1) Transceiver
1) AA   battery holder
2) AA batteries
1) User manual

 Specifications:
Operating frequency: 434.120Mhz 
Working Voltage: 2.1-3.5v \ 2x AA Alkaline batteries (Included)
Current consumption: 11mA
Stability: PLL (Phase-Locked Loop) controlled.

 Frequency: True NFM: Frequency range approximately: 434.050Mhz -434.120Mhz

 Distance: Long transmitting range, over 4000ft. Penetrates through walls and ceilings.

 Power: Up to 15mW RF output.

 Audio: Internal microphone manufactured by KEPO: 100Hz to 10,000Hz frequency range 

 Antenna: Flexible wire 18cm full extended.

 Adjustments: No adjustments are required.

 Works for 7 days when using 2 AA Duracell alkaline batteries 

 The unit comes fully assembled and ready for use, as shown in the picture.
 You just need to buy 2 x Duracell alkaline batteries.  
In testing this transmitter we used a transceiver and got a transmission range of well over 4000 feet!

To get the maximum range: 
The antenna should be stretched out straight and placed either horizontally or vertically.
 The receiving antenna must be in the same plane to get the maximum range and both 
 antennas should be as high as possible. The signal is generally not affected by brick walls, wooden walls, glass or plaster.
